<h2>Browser Security</h2>
<p>
  If you have work locally or use local resources, you could need to disable some security mechanism:
</p>

<h3>Chromium Family</h3>
<p>
  The Chromium browsers family allow you to disable security features that prevent you loading local resources as startup flags.
</p>
<ul>
  <li>[ext[disable-web-security|https://stackoverflow.com/questions/3102819/disable-same-origin-policy-in-chrome]]</li>
  <li>[ext[allow-file-access-from-files|https://dev.to/dengel29/loading-local-files-in-firefox-and-chrome-m9f]]</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <b>How-To</b> [ext[Run Chromium with flags|http://www.chromium.org/developers/how-tos/run-chromium-with-flags/]], in the location bar:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Input <b>&#x63;&#x68;&#x72;&#x6F;&#x6D;&#x65;&#x3A;&#x2F;&#x2F;&#x76;&#x65;&#x72;&#x73;&#x69;&#x6F;&#x6E;</b></li>
  <li>Check the enabled startup parameter flags.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Firefox</h3>
<p>
  In the location bar, input <b>about:config</b> to access Firefox <b>Advanced Preferences</b>.
</p>
<table>
  <tr>
    <td>[ext[privacy.file_unique_origin|https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/CORS/Errors/CORSRequestNotHttp]]</td>
